I found the source of the error. The problem lies in the qL and qR variables of bcfun for the coupled() function. The MATLAB documentation, see [here][1] and [here][2], is slightly ambiguous on whether the q&#39;s should be matrices or column vectors. I had used matrices
```matlab
        qL = [0 0;0 0];
        qR = [0 0;0 0];
```
but in reality I should have used column vectors
```matlab
        qL = [0;0];
        qR = [0;0];
```
Amazingly, pdpe didn&#39;t throw an error, and simply gave wrong results. This should perhaps be fixed by the developers.


  [1]: https://www.mathworks.com/help/matlab/ref/pdepe.html
  [2]: https://www.mathworks.com/help/matlab/math/partial-differential-equations.html

